WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.094 --> 00:00:01.198
Hello Facebook Ads people!

00:00:01.331 --> 00:00:02.336
My name is Konstantinos 

00:00:02.469 --> 00:00:04.071
and today is the day that

00:00:04.071 --> 00:00:05.457
we're going to discuss about

00:00:05.457 --> 00:00:09.149
the end of breakdown data reporting on the Facebook platform.

00:00:29.599 --> 00:00:31.680
The breakdown results are gone and

00:00:31.680 --> 00:00:33.160
they are never coming back,

00:00:33.160 --> 00:00:35.360
as facebook announced after the iOS changes.

00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:36.440
No God!

00:00:36.440 --> 00:00:37.440
Please no!

00:00:37.587 --> 00:00:38.320
NO!

00:00:38.440 --> 00:00:40.160
If you follow me on social media,

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:42.320
if you've read my book, you know that

00:00:42.320 --> 00:00:44.760
I love dynamic creative ads and open targeting.

00:00:44.920 --> 00:00:47.430
I love segmentation of different audiences and demographics,

00:00:47.430 --> 00:00:50.863
but I won't be able to break down the results of my ads anymore

00:00:50.863 --> 00:00:52.720
 in order to do this

00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:54.720
and this is actually devastating.

00:00:54.880 --> 00:00:57.080
With breakdown results, we were able to see

00:00:57.080 --> 00:00:59.000
which ages, placements and more

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:01.570
were working bringing sales or leads

00:01:01.570 --> 00:01:02.760
and that was amazing for me,

00:01:02.867 --> 00:01:05.120
my accounts and I bet for other people too.

00:01:05.480 --> 00:01:08.120
But now it is just gone and it is not comig back

00:01:08.120 --> 00:01:09.360
as Facebook announced.

00:01:09.680 --> 00:01:11.680
The breakdown of which dynamic creatives

00:01:11.680 --> 00:01:12.960
or copies are working,

00:01:12.960 --> 00:01:14.480
was discontinued for a period,

00:01:14.600 --> 00:01:16.008
but now it is back

00:01:16.008 --> 00:01:17.280
and I'm super happy about it.

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:21.560
One last thing that is really bothering me and

00:01:21.560 --> 00:01:24.400
I actually consider it one of the worst developments

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:25.680
on the platform is that

00:01:25.680 --> 00:01:28.000
the breakdown of results are not available anymore.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:29.200
Whaaat?!

00:01:29.200 --> 00:01:31.160
And because i'm so pissed about it,

00:01:31.160 --> 00:01:33.200
I'm going to do a whole video about this topic

00:01:35.680 --> 00:01:38.920
There is one thing that really really really bothers me the most,

00:01:39.280 --> 00:01:41.840
that the next time a Facebook representative talks to me

00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:43.600
about automatic placements

00:01:43.920 --> 00:01:45.760
I won't be able to rub in their face,

00:01:45.760 --> 00:01:48.240
the breakdown results of the placement showing that

00:01:48.240 --> 00:01:50.240
three or four placements actually work.

00:01:50.760 --> 00:01:52.840
The idea that I'm not able to do this anymore,

00:01:52.840 --> 00:01:54.280
drives me crazy.

00:01:54.760 --> 00:01:55.960
There's a small work around,

00:01:55.960 --> 00:01:57.760
but I'm still not super satisfied with it.

00:01:58.240 --> 00:02:00.160
Let's jump on my computer to show you,

00:02:00.160 --> 00:02:03.320
how to break down the results and how it used to look

00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:04.560
and how it looks now.

00:02:04.720 --> 00:02:09.160
So let me show you how the breakdown of results is working,

00:02:09.800 --> 00:02:12.120
now that we have the breakdown of results

00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:13.560
for the dynamic ads again.

00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:14.840
Thank God!

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:18.480
Okay, we can actually see how it used to look

00:02:18.480 --> 00:02:20.959
also for the age, placement and stuff.

00:02:20.959 --> 00:02:28.760
So I have this campaign from the last 30 days the results,

00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:33.120
we can see that it spent 5.5k okay?

00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:37.812
So if we come here on the dots, okay,  we can see the breakdown.

00:02:37.812 --> 00:02:40.282
If we see the breakdown by time,

00:02:40.282 --> 00:02:41.640
we don't want to see that but

00:02:41.640 --> 00:02:47.840
we used to be able to see that; the age, gender, and country,

00:02:48.520 --> 00:02:52.160
and also very important was the placement as I mentioned.

00:02:52.480 --> 00:02:53.688
 So let's go on the age.

00:02:53.688 --> 00:02:56.249
What can we see here?

00:02:56.249 --> 00:02:58.520
Nothing! We can see zero results okay,

00:02:58.520 --> 00:03:00.720
so we cannot understand where

00:03:00.720 --> 00:03:03.400
these 130 purchases are coming from,

00:03:03.400 --> 00:03:05.227
from which age.

00:03:05.227 --> 00:03:08.000
But there's a workaround as I said,

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.880
we can see how much money it was spent towards the ages.

00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:15.160
So we can understand from that,

00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:22.080
that if the sales are coming from 55-64, 65+ okay?

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:24.720
The purchases should be there okay because

00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:27.040
we spend more money towards these ages.

00:03:27.520 --> 00:03:30.960
Now, the big question is if my ads are working

00:03:31.520 --> 00:03:33.160
and I'm seeing the amount spent then

00:03:33.160 --> 00:03:35.080
I can understand that it's working because

00:03:35.080 --> 00:03:36.560
it's optimizing for these ages.

00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:41.200
Perfect! If my ads are not working what it's going to happen?

00:03:41.720 --> 00:03:45.360
Then you are helpless, that's the truth.

00:03:45.520 --> 00:03:48.600
And the point that I'm saying that

00:03:48.600 --> 00:03:50.920
not having the breakdown of results because

00:03:50.920 --> 00:03:53.280
we cannot see how Facebook is spending our money.

00:03:53.519 --> 00:03:54.280
It's tragic.

00:03:54.520 --> 00:03:55.521
It's because of that.

00:03:55.521 --> 00:03:57.440
Because if 65+

00:03:57.440 --> 00:04:00.600
for example it's spending a lot of money, but

00:04:00.600 --> 00:04:02.720
it's not giving you the cost per acquisition that

00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:04.400
you want in order to be profitable,

00:04:04.880 --> 00:04:06.360
maybe in your next ads and

00:04:06.360 --> 00:04:09.480
this is what we used to do back in the spring,

00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:11.600
we were able to actually say

00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:13.520
"Okay I'm not going to target 65+, 

00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:15.840
I'm going to go untill 64."

00:04:16.240 --> 00:04:17.960
So now this option is gone.

00:04:19.400 --> 00:04:24.320
Also another thing is the breakdown of

00:04:24.320 --> 00:04:25.497
the placement.

00:04:25.497 --> 00:04:27.200
This is very important for me

00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:29.040
because when it comes to placements,

00:04:29.040 --> 00:04:31.600
I like to use Instagram Feed, Facebook Feed,

00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:35.480
Instagram Stories, maybe Facebook Stories.

00:04:35.707 --> 00:04:37.560
And now, of course, we have the reels that

00:04:37.560 --> 00:04:39.880
we are all testing and we will see

00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:41.800
what's going to happen with them but

00:04:42.920 --> 00:04:44.280
everything else that Facebook says

00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:45.600
if you talk with a representative,

00:04:46.520 --> 00:04:48.100
